HEADWORD: Eucairite
<hw>Eu*cai"rite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
seasonable, opportune; <grk>e'y^</grk> well, good + <?/ season.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A metallic mineral, a selenide of copper and
silver; -- so called by Berzelius on account of its being found soon
after the discovery of the metal selenium.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

